He's cutting out wedges
from the nectarine.

726
00:29:46,384 --> 00:29:47,819
-In a half-moon shape.
-Why are you doing that?

727
00:29:47,886 --> 00:29:49,387
I want to make it pretty.

728
00:29:49,454 --> 00:29:50,488
For the shape?

729
00:29:50,555 --> 00:29:53,491
I learned that from the kitchen lady
when I part-timed at a bar.

730
00:29:54,058 --> 00:29:55,660
-The kitchen lady taught me.
-Right.

731
00:29:55,727 --> 00:29:58,863
-You can make rabbits with apples.
-Yes.

732
00:29:59,764 --> 00:30:01,399
He's using that?

733
00:30:02,467 --> 00:30:06,237
He's slicing the stem of the romaine.

734
00:30:07,238 --> 00:30:09,140
CLEANING UP RIGHT AWAY

735
00:30:09,207 --> 00:30:10,708
He's really neat.

736
00:30:10,775 --> 00:30:12,343
Yes, he is.

737
00:30:12,410 --> 00:30:14,445
He's using burrata.

738
00:30:14,512 --> 00:30:16,347
I think he's using just the center.

739
00:30:16,414 --> 00:30:18,716
-The softest part.
-The soft part, like a poached egg.

740
00:30:18,783 --> 00:30:21,820
He made a shape with the burrata.

741
00:30:21,886 --> 00:30:23,855
It's going into the fridge.

742
00:30:23,922 --> 00:30:25,223
He's cooling it down.

743
00:30:25,290 --> 00:30:26,357
AGAIN, KEEPING IT COLD

744
00:30:27,258 --> 00:30:29,194
-It's ready.
-He's ready to go.

745
00:30:29,260 --> 00:30:32,997
Would it become flat if he fried
beaten eggs? I've never seen it.

746
00:30:33,064 --> 00:30:34,199
HOW WILL IT TURN OUT?

747
00:30:36,434 --> 00:30:38,269
The eggs don't look so bad.

748
00:30:38,336 --> 00:30:43,975
-Kyung-soo's eyes are only on Poong.
-That's impossible.

749
00:30:44,475 --> 00:30:45,410
That's impossible.

750
00:30:45,476 --> 00:30:49,314
-He said it'd turn out like fried tofu.
-It looks fascinating.

751
00:30:49,380 --> 00:30:51,716
They look like clouds in the sky.

752
00:30:51,783 --> 00:30:53,518
-You're right.
-It's fascinating.

753
00:30:53,585 --> 00:30:56,754
I've never seen
such a pretty dish made by him.

754
00:30:56,821 --> 00:31:00,425
-He has never decorated his dishes.
-It's fascinating.

755
00:31:00,491 --> 00:31:02,193
All we ever saw was poop loaches.

756
00:31:03,394 --> 00:31:05,296
THE TOP CHEF OF A FINE DINING RESTAURANT
CAN'T STAY STILL

757
00:31:05,363 --> 00:31:07,832
HE BEGINS TO MAKE CRUMBS

758
00:31:08,399 --> 00:31:11,936
He's chopping anchovies,
almonds, and biscuits.

759
00:31:12,003 --> 00:31:14,405
I think he's making crumbs.

760
00:31:14,472 --> 00:31:16,774
He's using anchovies,
almonds, and biscuits.

761
00:31:17,809 --> 00:31:19,244
He's using two knives!

762
00:31:19,310 --> 00:31:20,144
THE SIGNATURE TECHNIQUE

763
00:31:20,211 --> 00:31:21,246
He's using two knives!

764
00:31:21,312 --> 00:31:22,547
Whoa!

765
00:31:22,614 --> 00:31:23,948
Two knives!

766
00:31:24,015 --> 00:31:25,783
He's using two knives!

767
00:31:25,850 --> 00:31:28,453
THE ESSENCE OF A FINE DINING EXPERIENCE

768
00:31:30,088 --> 00:31:31,322
Double knives.

769
00:31:31,923 --> 00:31:34,125
-He chopped them quickly.
-He's fast.

770
00:31:34,192 --> 00:31:36,127
He's using two knives.

771
00:31:36,194 --> 00:31:38,463
He's using those to add texture.

772
00:31:38,529 --> 00:31:40,798
Is it to add texture to the sauce?

773
00:31:40,865 --> 00:31:43,234
Jung-hwan, they have five minutes left.

774
00:31:43,301 --> 00:31:45,236
-Shall I?
-Please go out.

775
00:31:45,303 --> 00:31:47,205
Please go to the kitchen.

776
00:31:47,272 --> 00:31:49,407
3. BOIL FRIED EGGS IN HOT WATER
TO REMOVE GREASE

777
00:31:49,474 --> 00:31:52,143
Can you try Poong's fried eggs?

778
00:31:52,210 --> 00:31:53,411
-Do I have to?
-Yes.

779
00:31:53,478 --> 00:31:54,612
HESITANT

780
00:31:54,679 --> 00:31:56,281
I wonder what it'll be like.

781
00:31:56,347 --> 00:31:58,216
-Try a bite.
-It looks like noodles.

782
00:31:58,283 --> 00:31:59,684
It seems tough.

783
00:31:59,751 --> 00:32:01,019
-All right.
-I need cold water.

784
00:32:01,085 --> 00:32:02,887
-It's called Egg Love Shot.
-Whoa.

785
00:32:02,954 --> 00:32:03,788
He's spilling everything.

786
00:32:03,855 --> 00:32:05,323
I have to cook there later.

787
00:32:05,390 --> 00:32:07,091
CHUCKLING

788
00:32:07,158 --> 00:32:09,961
What are the eggs like?

789
00:32:10,028 --> 00:32:12,030
He tries a bite.

790
00:32:12,530 --> 00:32:15,400
Does it taste like a love shot
or a headshot?

791
00:32:16,567 --> 00:32:17,702
-It's…
-A headshot?

792
00:32:17,769 --> 00:32:19,203
It's a headshot.

793
00:32:20,538 --> 00:32:22,707
What? He should be thrown out then!

794
00:32:22,774 --> 00:32:26,277
It's like the crunchy edges
of a fried egg.

795
00:32:26,344 --> 00:32:27,211
It has a great texture.

796
00:32:27,278 --> 00:32:30,848
Poong said he wanted to make it
taste like fried tofu.

797
00:32:30,915 --> 00:32:33,418
He needs more time
to make it like fried tofu.

798
00:32:33,484 --> 00:32:34,953
I've just begun.

799
00:32:35,019 --> 00:32:36,988
-He'll make it good now.
-I see.

800
00:32:37,055 --> 00:32:40,124
I'm smelling
something delicious on this side.

801
00:32:40,191 --> 00:32:41,159
Thanks.

802
00:32:41,926 --> 00:32:43,828
The honeycomb shapes are done.

803
00:32:43,895 --> 00:32:45,763
He didn't have enough time
to make the tuiles.

804
00:32:46,364 --> 00:32:47,732
THE TUILES ARE A SUCCESS

805
00:32:47,799 --> 00:32:49,534
They look good.

806
00:32:49,600 --> 00:32:50,902
They look so pretty.

807
00:32:50,969 --> 00:32:52,570
-The tuiles look excellent.
-They're so pretty.

808
00:32:53,137 --> 00:32:55,073
HEADING STRAIGHT TO THE FRIDGE

809
00:32:56,040 --> 00:32:58,376
HE BRINGS BACK
THE INGREDIENTS HE LEFT INSIDE

810
00:32:59,210 --> 00:33:00,378
CUTTING THE BOTTOM PORTION

811
00:33:00,445 --> 00:33:02,413
Jong-won is getting ready
to serve his food.

812
00:33:03,281 --> 00:33:05,116
It looks so pretty.

813
00:33:05,183 --> 00:33:08,219
The nectarines look pretty.

814
00:33:08,286 --> 00:33:10,955
The grill marks look wonderful.

815
00:33:11,022 --> 00:33:13,057
Gosh, it looks so good.

816
00:33:13,124 --> 00:33:14,559
It's incredible.

817
00:33:14,625 --> 00:33:16,894
It looks so good.

818
00:33:16,961 --> 00:33:20,999
The balance is great too.
Burrata goes very well with fruit.

819
00:33:21,065 --> 00:33:22,066
Do you see the sauce?

820
00:33:22,133 --> 00:33:23,801
-The sauce.
-Can you try that?

821
00:33:24,369 --> 00:33:26,270
YUM

822
00:33:26,337 --> 00:33:29,107
How's the nectarine sauce?

823
00:33:29,173 --> 00:33:31,776
-Gosh.
-Does it have good vibes?

824
00:33:31,843 --> 00:33:33,444
It has good vibes.

825
00:33:33,511 --> 00:33:35,513
It's refreshing. It has good vibes.

826
00:33:35,580 --> 00:33:38,316
-Summer will melt away at this rate.
-It has good vibes.

827
00:33:38,383 --> 00:33:39,517
Gosh, I love it.

828
00:33:40,084 --> 00:33:43,087
DRAINING THE MSG VEGETABLE BROTH

829
00:33:43,654 --> 00:33:45,123
4. ADDING ICE TO THE BROTH AND MAKE SOUP

830
00:33:45,189 --> 00:33:47,058
-You have three minutes.
-Three minutes.

831
00:33:47,125 --> 00:33:48,626
He won't have enough time.

832
00:33:48,693 --> 00:33:49,594
Wait, look at the time.

833
00:33:49,660 --> 00:33:52,063
Don't you need
cucumbers and perilla leaves?

834
00:33:52,130 --> 00:33:53,998
-I haven't chopped anything.
-You need to.

835
00:33:54,065 --> 00:33:55,833
-Cucumbers and perilla leaves.
-Three minutes.

836
00:33:55,900 --> 00:33:57,869
It's so chaotic here.

837
00:33:58,436 --> 00:34:01,939
5. ADD CHOPPED ONION INTO THE COLD SOUP

838
00:34:02,006 --> 00:34:04,108
Can you ask him to try the soup?

839
00:34:04,175 --> 00:34:06,010
-Hey, Jung-hwan!
-Yes?

840
00:34:06,077 --> 00:34:10,114
Kyung-soo asks you
to try the soup Poong is making.

841
00:34:10,181 --> 00:34:12,750
-Kyung-soo asked you?
-Yes, he asked me himself.

842
00:34:12,817 --> 00:34:15,787
-He wants to know how the soup is.
-The soup?

843
00:34:15,853 --> 00:34:17,355
Try that soup with onion.

844
00:34:17,422 --> 00:34:19,090
-The soup?
-The soup.

845
00:34:19,157 --> 00:34:20,958
I don't think he's done yet.

846
00:34:21,025 --> 00:34:24,128
The soup looks the most important.
You have a minute and 50 seconds.

847
00:34:24,195 --> 00:34:26,063
-And?
-All right.

848
00:34:26,130 --> 00:34:28,199
-But it looks good.
-Tell us what it's like.

849
00:34:28,266 --> 00:34:30,168
Isn't this detergent foam?

850
00:34:31,469 --> 00:34:32,637
Detergent foam?

851
00:34:32,703 --> 00:34:34,472
It's like the foam from detergent.

852
00:34:34,539 --> 00:34:37,141
Let me try the soup.
I'm not sure what it is.

853
00:34:37,208 --> 00:34:39,844
What's the soup like?

854
00:34:39,911 --> 00:34:41,012
-Huh?
-Yes?

855
00:34:41,579 --> 00:34:42,647
-It must be good.
-A love shot.

856
00:34:43,781 --> 00:34:46,784
-It's <i>naengmyeon</i> broth.
-<i>Naengmyeon</i>?

857
00:34:46,851 --> 00:34:49,353
Wait, I can taste the MSG!

858
00:34:50,455 --> 00:34:51,856
SAVORY TASTE GUARANTEED

859
00:34:51,923 --> 00:34:54,492
It's a love shot for now!

860
00:34:54,559 --> 00:34:55,493
It looks like noodles.

861
00:34:55,560 --> 00:34:58,229
I like it. But look at this.

862
00:34:58,296 --> 00:34:59,931
-The eggs became noodles.
-It looks like noodles.

863
00:34:59,997 --> 00:35:02,133
-It looks like <i>naengmyeon</i>.
-You're right.

864
00:35:02,200 --> 00:35:04,335
-<i>Naengmyeon.</i>
-Egg <i>naengmyeon</i>.

865
00:35:05,903 --> 00:35:07,672
JONG-WON ALMOST FINISHED SERVING HIS DISH

866
00:35:08,439 --> 00:35:10,808
NECTARINE

867
00:35:12,577 --> 00:35:16,280
ROMAINE

868
00:35:16,848 --> 00:35:20,384
APPLE MINT

869
00:35:20,952 --> 00:35:25,189
FINISHING OFF WITH SALT AND PEPPER

870
00:35:25,256 --> 00:35:27,625
Chef Jong-won is almost done.

871
00:35:27,692 --> 00:35:29,627
-You have a minute left!
-One minute!

872
00:35:30,194 --> 00:35:31,929
JONG-WON GRABS ICE

873
00:35:34,098 --> 00:35:36,000
