874
00:35:36,067 --> 00:35:39,537
-What is that? What's he doing?
-He's grinding ice.

875
00:35:39,604 --> 00:35:41,939
-It's to serve his food.
-As the presentation?

876
00:35:42,006 --> 00:35:43,941
He'll serve the dressing over ice.

877
00:35:44,008 --> 00:35:46,310
-After grinding the ice?
-He wants to serve it cold.

878
00:35:46,878 --> 00:35:49,347
HE RIPS THE TOMATO PEEL WITH HIS HANDS

879
00:35:49,413 --> 00:35:50,615
AND CHOPS A CUCUMBER

880
00:35:50,681 --> 00:35:51,749
You have 45 seconds.

881
00:35:51,816 --> 00:35:54,519
Poong chops perilla leaves.

882
00:35:54,585 --> 00:35:57,155
-They didn't get chopped.
-Not at all.

883
00:35:57,221 --> 00:35:59,624
He kept them in one piece on purpose.

884
00:35:59,690 --> 00:36:01,526
-It's like hand-pulled noodles.
-Thirty seconds!

885
00:36:01,592 --> 00:36:02,927
The leaves weren't chopped.

886
00:36:02,994 --> 00:36:05,029
-Everything is connected.
-Thirty seconds!

887
00:36:05,096 --> 00:36:06,597
Thirty seconds!

888
00:36:06,664 --> 00:36:08,966
Gosh, this is so hectic.

889
00:36:09,934 --> 00:36:11,736
Just like that.

890
00:36:11,802 --> 00:36:13,037
Look.

891
00:36:13,104 --> 00:36:14,739
It looks so summery.

892
00:36:14,805 --> 00:36:16,807
-He's serving the sauce cold.
-It's sitting on ice.

893
00:36:16,874 --> 00:36:18,776
Everything here is clean,

894
00:36:18,843 --> 00:36:21,846
but this side is just…

895
00:36:21,913 --> 00:36:23,748
-Fifteen seconds.
-He should clean up.

896
00:36:23,814 --> 00:36:25,883
-He should clean up.
-Fifteen seconds left.

897
00:36:25,950 --> 00:36:28,953
Look at all these pieces
of green onion flying around.

898
00:36:29,020 --> 00:36:30,588
-Fifteen seconds left.
-Look at all these pieces

899
00:36:30,655 --> 00:36:32,623
-of green onion flying around.
-And the tuile?

900
00:36:32,690 --> 00:36:34,959
-What about the tuile?
-The tuile.

901
00:36:35,026 --> 00:36:37,161
-The tuile.
-Seven. Six.

902
00:36:37,228 --> 00:36:39,363
-He's picking one.
-Five. Four.

903
00:36:39,430 --> 00:36:41,065
-Three. Two.
-Three. Two.

904
00:36:41,132 --> 00:36:43,434
-Three. Two. One.
-Three. Two. One.

905
00:36:43,501 --> 00:36:44,969
DESTROYING THE SPRING ONION

906
00:36:45,036 --> 00:36:46,237
CHOPPING

907
00:36:46,304 --> 00:36:48,172
-Two. One.
-Two. One.

908
00:36:48,239 --> 00:36:49,240
THE TRUE MEANING OF CHAOTIC DINING

909
00:36:49,307 --> 00:36:51,909
-Time's up!
-Time's up! It's over.

910
00:36:51,976 --> 00:36:53,411
Poong finishes first,

911
00:36:53,477 --> 00:36:55,112
followed by Jong-won.

912
00:36:55,179 --> 00:36:56,847
-Gosh.
-Bravo!

913
00:36:56,914 --> 00:36:58,416
What's this?

914
00:36:58,482 --> 00:36:59,517
FALLING OVER

915
00:36:59,584 --> 00:37:01,786
Wait, what is this?

916
00:37:02,453 --> 00:37:03,821
TOPPED WITH POONG'S CHILI OIL

917
00:37:03,888 --> 00:37:06,090
Did he pour chili oil over the soup?

918
00:37:06,157 --> 00:37:08,159
I can already tell what it'll be like.

919
00:37:08,226 --> 00:37:09,594
What if that's good?

920
00:37:09,660 --> 00:37:11,128
He added three condiments.

921
00:37:11,195 --> 00:37:12,563
It looks good.

922
00:37:12,630 --> 00:37:14,498
-It does.
-It must be.

923
00:37:14,565 --> 00:37:15,733
I'm hungry.

924
00:37:16,234 --> 00:37:18,970
<i>This is</i>
<i>Webtoon Artist Poong's Egg Love Shot.</i>

925
00:37:19,036 --> 00:37:23,874
AN ICED COLD SOUP
WITH NEVER-BEFORE-SEEN FRIED EGGS

926
00:37:24,508 --> 00:37:28,246
WEBTOON ARTIST KIM POONG'S EGG LOVE SHOT

927
00:37:28,312 --> 00:37:30,348
He must've poured chili oil over the soup.

928
00:37:30,414 --> 00:37:31,983
Yes, I topped it with chili oil.

929
00:37:32,049 --> 00:37:34,819
But because of the cherry tomatoes,

930
00:37:34,885 --> 00:37:38,356
the perilla leaves and the spring onion…

931
00:37:38,422 --> 00:37:39,790
-You can't eat it?
-…it smells good.

932
00:37:39,857 --> 00:37:40,891
-What?
-You can't eat it?

933
00:37:41,459 --> 00:37:43,227
Come on, don't say that.

934
00:37:43,294 --> 00:37:47,632
-Come on, Manager Park.
-Come on, Mr. Park.

935
00:37:47,698 --> 00:37:51,335
He was just about to eat it.
Why did you ask if he couldn't?

936
00:37:51,402 --> 00:37:52,770
Unlike my expectation,

937
00:37:52,837 --> 00:37:54,739
-Does it smell good?
-it smells like a decent cold dish.

938
00:37:54,805 --> 00:37:56,207
Does it smell good?

939
00:37:56,274 --> 00:37:58,876
-It must smell rather fresh.
-It's just MSG.

940
00:37:58,943 --> 00:38:01,679
-Sir, please don't hold such a prejudice.
-I won't.

941
00:38:01,746 --> 00:38:02,613
I'll keep my heart open.

942
00:38:02,680 --> 00:38:04,248
-Thank you for the food.
-Sure.

943
00:38:04,315 --> 00:38:06,350
The fridge owner gets the first taste.

944
00:38:06,417 --> 00:38:08,185
-May I try the soup first?
-May he do that?

945
00:38:08,252 --> 00:38:10,121
-That sounds great.
-He tries the soup.

946
00:38:10,187 --> 00:38:11,422
-It must be good.
-This is it.

947
00:38:11,489 --> 00:38:13,190
SLURP

948
00:38:13,257 --> 00:38:15,860
Jung-hwan tried it on his behalf.

949
00:38:15,926 --> 00:38:18,362
-It's seasoned perfectly.
-I see.

950
00:38:18,429 --> 00:38:20,865
He says it's seasoned perfectly.

951
00:38:20,931 --> 00:38:22,433
Also,

952
00:38:22,500 --> 00:38:24,001
it's really savory.

953
00:38:24,068 --> 00:38:26,470
Why is that the case?
Because of the vegetables?

954
00:38:26,537 --> 00:38:28,973
-He used vegetable stock.
-I'm glad he did.

955
00:38:29,040 --> 00:38:30,841
He used vegetables for the first time.

956
00:38:30,908 --> 00:38:33,044
It looked deliciously golden.

957
00:38:33,110 --> 00:38:35,146
Should I top this with everything?

958
00:38:35,212 --> 00:38:37,448
Just enjoy it however you like.

959
00:38:37,515 --> 00:38:40,885
-It's like cold acorn jelly soup and rice.
-Eat everything as you like.

960
00:38:40,951 --> 00:38:44,221
-It looks good.
-Manager Park is kind of nosy.

961
00:38:44,288 --> 00:38:47,158
I can't sit around quietly
now that I'm here.

962
00:38:47,224 --> 00:38:49,493
He really reminds me
of a manager at an office.

963
00:38:49,560 --> 00:38:51,662
-Make me the executive director.
-Let me try some.

964
00:38:52,530 --> 00:38:53,898
-Try some.
-The executive director.

965
00:38:53,964 --> 00:38:55,466
-Executive director?
-He wants to be that.

966
00:38:55,533 --> 00:38:57,668
Kyung-soo tries a bite.

967
00:38:57,735 --> 00:38:58,936
A guy who's serious about cooking.

968
00:38:59,003 --> 00:39:00,171
APPRECIATING THE FLAVOR

969
00:39:01,072 --> 00:39:03,541
-Wait, this is good.
-Is it?

970
00:39:03,607 --> 00:39:05,109
